RIYADH: The UAE intends to list the Salik road toll system on the Dubai financial market, Asharq reported on Saturday. UAE’s Finance Minister Sheikh Maktoum bin Mohammed bin Rashid Al-Maktoum, who is also Dubai’s deputy ruler, wrote in a tweet: “At the Committee for the Development of Capital Markets and Exchanges in Dubai, we approved a plan for the listing of the electronic toll road system (Salik) on the Dubai Financial Market. Salik is a successful project with huge investment potential.”